Modifications relative to the kiper292/wireguard-turn-android upstream
----------------------------------------------------------------------

* Removed all Android-specific JNI bindings and cgo entry points.
* Replaced `wgProtectSocket(int fd)` C calls with a Go-only
  `SocketProtector` interface (pkg/wgturn.SocketProtector).
* Replaced `__android_log_write` with a Go `Logger` interface.
* De-globalised the proxy: each `Hub` is its own instance, no package-level
  state, multiple Hubs per process supported.
* Repackaged into `pkg/` (public API) and `internal/` (implementation),
  removing the upstream `package main` flat layout.
* Stripped browser-fingerprint TLS-Client dependency tree
  (github.com/kiper292/tls-client and friends) for v0.0.1-alpha. The
  default `CredentialsProvider` is a stub; real VK / WB providers will be
  re-introduced in subsequent releases as separate sub-modules to keep the
  core dependency surface small.


